    <section id="directions" class="bg-white">
      <h2 class="section-heading how-it-works navy-text center">How to get there?</h2>
          <div class="container">
              <div class="col-md-8">
                <p class="about-tahoe navy-text">
                Like most places in the year 2017, you can plug in any ski resort or hotel to <a href="maps.google.com">Google Maps</a>, and you won't be disappointed. If you end up taking a lesson with us, all of our lessons for the '16/17 season take place </b> at <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Homewood+Mountain+Resort/@39.0855833,-120.1627278,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x80997fda4762005f:0x73b0c46aa0c1068d!8m2!3d39.0855833!4d-120.1605391" class="green-link">Homewood Mountain Resort</a>, which is located on the west shore of Lake Tahoe, 10 minutes from Tahoe city.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="maps-container row">
                  <iframe
                  width="350"
                  height="160"
                  frameborder="0"
                  src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=<%= ENV["GOOGLE_MAPS_API"] %>
                    &q=Homewood+Mountain+Resor" allowfullscreen>
                </iframe>
                </div>
              </div>
           <div class="col-md-12">
              <hr class="deposit-hr-navy">
            </div>
              <h3 class="navy-text">
                  Additionally, here are a few other things worth keeping in mind about traveling to Tahoe:
              </h3>
               <ul class="north-vs-south navy-text">
                    <li> There's only two main highways in or out. <b> Interstate 80</b> is the primary route for those visiting North Tahoe, while <b> Highway 50</b> is the road to get into South Lake Tahoe. I-80 is two lanes each direction the whole way, which means it can accommodate a bit more traffic flow, but it is also a major trucking route, so you will have to deal with passing trucks slowly makign the climb. US-50 is one lane each way once you get past the foothills, with occasional passing lanes.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    </li>
                    <li> Both major highways are subject to <a href="http://www.dot.ca.gov/hq/roadinfo/chcontrl.htm" class="green-link">chain control</a> almost anytime that it snows, and do occasionally close down completely due to unsafe visibility or avalanche risk. </li>
                    <br>
                    <li> For those new to winter driving, <b> chains </b> are like metal crampons for your tires, to help with traction on snow and ice. When chain control is in effect, there will be a check point operated by CalTrans where you will be forced to put on chains (and buy them if you don't have any) in order to proceed, unless you have a vehicle with 4-wheel drive and snow tires.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    </li>
                    <li> It's always best to check <a href="/road-conditions" class="green-link"> road conditions</a> before your trip. You can also <a href="https://twitter.com/snowschoolers" class="btn btn-default twitter">follow us on Twitter</a> to get crucial updates about road conditions.</li>
              </ul>
          </div>
